The horror figures with dead eyes, sharp teeth and blood spattered beards are appearing on patios and decks across the UK, defying the posh RHS bar on letting them into its hallowed grounds. Traditional fishing gnomes, cheeky bum baring versions and planters are also proving popular, according to eBay.Gnome fan David Lewis, head gardener at The Roof Gardens in Kensington and multi-award winning Chelsea gardener said: Gardens are an expression of your own style.